# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Book Social Network — Docker Compose Environment Variables
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in your real secret values
#   3. docker-compose up -d  (Docker Compose automatically reads .env)
#
# PRODUCTION UPGRADE:
#   Replace all localhost/127.0.0.1 values with your real domain/IP.
#   MinIO file URLs are stored as RELATIVE PATHS in the DB (e.g. "covers/uuid.jpg").
#   Each client (mobile/web/admin) rebuilds the full URL from its own MINIO_PUBLIC_URL.
#   → No DB migration needed when switching environments.
#
# This file is gitignored. NEVER commit .env with real secrets.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── JWT Secret ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HMAC-SHA512 signing key. MUST be the same across ALL services & restarts.
# Generate a strong key: openssl rand -base64 64
JWT_SIGNER_KEY=change-me-generate-with-openssl-rand-base64-64

# ── Email Provider (Brevo / Sendinblue) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Sign up at https://www.brevo.com/ and get your API key
BREVO_API_KEY=xkeysib-your-real-brevo-api-key-here

# ── MinIO (Object Storage) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MINIO_ROOT_USER=minioadmin
MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD=minioadmin
MINIO_BUCKET_NAME=book-social-network

# ── Database Passwords ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root
NEO4J_PASSWORD=12345678

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# URL / DOMAIN CONFIGURATION
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# ARCHITECTURE NOTE:
#   Files are stored in MinIO with RELATIVE object keys (e.g. "covers/uuid.jpg").
#   The DB never stores absolute URLs — only relative paths.
#   Each client builds the full URL:
#     fullUrl = {MINIO_PUBLIC_URL}/{bucket}/{objectKey}
#
# ── MinIO Internal (Docker service-to-service) ────────────────────────────────
#   Production: replace with internal hostname if MinIO is on a separate server
MINIO_ENDPOINT=http://minio:9000
